# Frontend Next.js - Critical Rules Summary

Full guides: `docs/conventions/frontend/`. Read the relevant file before editing.

## Ten Critical Rules

### 1. Server Components by Default

Pages and data reads MUST use Server Components unless the UI needs browser APIs or event handlers. Every `"use client"` MUST have a comment explaining why.

### 2. Thin `page.tsx` Shells

Route files MUST only parse `params`/`searchParams`, call `notFound()`, and render a domain entry from `domain/{feature}/`.

### 3. No Cross-Domain Imports

`domain/posts/` MUST NOT import from `domain/authors/`. Promote shared code to `@/shared/` or `components/ui/`. See `07-domain-boundaries.md`.

### 4. Typed API Client Only

HTTP calls MUST use `getApiClient()` with openapi-typescript paths. MUST NOT use Axios or ad-hoc `fetch` URLs in domain code.

### 5. Server Actions for Form Mutations

Form posts MUST use Server Actions with Zod validation in the action file, not client-side-only POST handlers.

### 6. TanStack Query for Server State

Server data MUST use TanStack Query or Server Component props. MUST NOT store server data in Zustand or load it in `useEffect`.

### 7. No Manual Memoization

When React Compiler is enabled, MUST NOT add `useMemo`, `useCallback`, or `React.memo`.

### 8. Playwright for Journeys

Every happy-path user journey MUST have a Playwright test in `apps/web/e2e/` using roles or `data-testid`.

### 9. proxy.ts Is Not Security

`proxy.ts` MUST only check cookie presence. Authoritative auth belongs in Server Components and Server Actions.

### 10. Complete UI States

Domain pages MUST render loading, empty, error, and forbidden states. MUST NOT ship blank placeholders.
